<main class="home">
  <div class="intro-home">
    <h2>Greetings!</h2>
    <p>Welcome! I am Todd, I am a web designer &amp; developer from South Portland, Maine and I love creating things on the web. This is my personal site where I write about technology, web, and other things I run across. I may also write about my misadventures when traveling. Have a look around and enjoy!</p>
  </div>

  <article class="about-intro">
    <div class="home-container">
      <div class="home-img"><img src="/img/headshot.png" alt="Headshot of Todd" class="lazyload"></div>
        <h3>I have an obsession with learning things on the web. I am currently re-sharpening my Vanilla JavaScript skills, learning Vue and React, playing around with Gatsby, immersed in some User Experience courses. I just finished and became certified in a W3C Introduction to Accessibility course and I am very passionate about accessibility on the web as well as diversity and inclusion. Some say it is a sickness, I say it is just another day at the office.</h3>
    </div>
  </article>

  <div class="articles">
    <h3>Latest Articles</h3>
      <ul class="article-sections">
        <li class="article-wrapper">
